An agreement on the payment of social grants has been reached between the Department of Social Development, the South African Social Security Agency (Sassa) and Cash Paymaster Services.&nbsp;Following three days of talks, Department of Social Development spokeswoman Lumka Oliphant said minister Bathabile Dlamini would announce the nature of the agreement in due course. With a month to go until the contract with CPS expires, there is still uncertainty about how more than 17-million social grants will be paid on April 1